                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.943 Manchuria/43: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-24T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 24, 1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 25—3
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>843. Department’s 382, November 28, 3 p.m. Following from Mukden: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“No. 16, December 23, 3 p.m. Reference Department’s No. 380 and 382 to
                            the Embassy November 26, 2 p.m., and November 28, 3 p.m.</p>
                        <p>This Office today received a letter from the Chief of the Political
                            Bureau of the Foreign Office stating that foreign juridical persons
                            established for profit whose object is to do business in Manchuria
                            ‘must’ be established as new juridical persons established and
                            registered under Manchukuo law.</p>
                        <p>There are two such American firms in Mukden.</p>
                        <p>Instructions are requested as to what reply if any is to be made to the
                            Foreign Office.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Harbin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
